		<strong>Alpine Competitor U10 and under - $25 </strong><br>
		<strong>Alpine Competitor U12 and under - $50 </strong><br>
		<strong>Alpine Competitor U14 and under - $80 </strong><br>
		<strong>Alpine Competitor U16 and over - $150 (Required for FIS registration) </strong><br>
		
		<p><strong>U.S. Ski & Snowboard General Member ($20):</strong>  The low-cost U.S. Ski & Snowboard General membership is designed for young athletes who are training with a club program are not yet competing in U.S. Ski & Snowboard competitions other than USCSA/U.S. Ski & Snowboard dual sanctioned events. 
		Other non-U.S. Ski & Snowboard events participation may include USCSA, high school events and forerunning U.S. Ski & Snowboard and non-U.S. Ski & Snowboard events. It's also perfect for club volunteers or parents who are starting to become active in support of club activities and events. Not intended for those in a position of authority over minors.		
		
		<p><strong>U.S. Ski & Snowboard Master ($100):</strong> For ages 18 and over prior to Dec. 31. The U.S. Ski & Snowboard Masters membership gives alpine athletes over the age of 18 access to alpine masters events, including Masters Championships and its qualifying events. 
		This membership is perfect for adult athletes who are interested in competing with other adults domestically. Required for alpine masters FIS registration.		
		
